            . I am a <rs id="t18230910-306-viclabel1645" type="occupation">journeyman tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-306-victim2641 t18230910-306-viclabel1645"></join>. On the 4th of August, between three and four o'clock in the afternoon, I was walking in the <placeName id="t18230910-306-crimeloc1646">Hampstead-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-306-crimeloc1646" type="placeName" value="Hampstead-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-306-crimeloc1646" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-306-off1643 t18230910-306-crimeloc1646"></join>; the prisoner came up and asked me for some halfpence - she had two little girls with her. She followed me a long while, and said they had nothing to eat - and I said I had no halfpence. I put my hand into my pocket, pulled out my money - I had some silver and copper together; the prisoner snatched two half-crowns out of my hand and ran off. I followed and overtook her in five minutes, without losing sight of her; she had not ran far; I took one half-crown from her hand, but could not find the other. I did not see her searched, but the other was found upon her - I was sober - I knew nothing of her before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-306-person2643">
